'''Proteins''' are consumable items that increase the Attack gained by a Pokémon after breeding by 1 for each Protein given. Each Pokémon can consume a total of 5 proteins per unlocked region. They can be purchased from each [[Regions|Region's]] Pokémon League, traded for using [[Berries]] with the [[Berry Master]] of each region from [[Johto]] onwards, and found in [[Dungeons]]. 

==How to Use==
Go to Start Menu > Items > Item Bag, select the protein and select a Pokémon to use it on. Once used, the effect is permanent and cannot be removed. Additionally, Proteins used do not retroactively boost a Pokémon's damage. Therefore, it is beneficial to use Proteins on a Pokémon as soon as possible.

==New Efficiency==
Below is a list of the most efficient Pokémon to breed accounting for both the Regional Damage Debuff and Proteins.  Breeding efficiency is determined by the following formula:

<math> \colorbox{White}{$ \text{Egg Cycles} = \frac{\text{Egg Steps}}{40} $}</math>

<math>\colorbox{White}{$ \text{Breeding Efficiency} = \frac{0.25 \times \text{Base Attack} + \text{Proteins Used}}{\text{Egg Cycles}} $} </math>

Linked [https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1X5lBpoGCC6hc9ogzCEJGh87ecFCvLSJ1LqTe1FSiVKQ/edit?usp=sharing here] is a spreadsheet that calculates the best Pokémon to breed given an inputted amount of Proteins and factoring in the Regional Debuff to Pokémon Attack.

==Price==

When bought from the Indigo Plateau / Pokémon League, the price for a Protein rises irreversibly, similar to [[Master Ball|Master Balls]]. The initial price starts at 10,000 {{pdollar}}, and increments by a factor of 1.1 every purchase before capping at 1,000,000 {{pdollar}} which is 49 purchases.

